org.opennaas.extensions.idb.database
Class TransactionManager

java.lang.Object
  org.opennaas.extensions.idb.database.TransactionManager
Direct Known Subclasses:
TransactionManagerDelete
public abstract class TransactionManager
extends java.lang.Object

This class takes care of accessing the database in a nice and tidy way. It opens a session, opens a transaction in this session, executes a database operation, commits the transaction, and closes the session. If anything goes wrong, the transaction is rolled back and a DatabaseException is thrown. The actual database operation is not part of this class, but is an abstract method dbOperation() that has to be defined in a child class.

Author:
Christian de Waal
